seal               : A single cell with a whipping tail ringed by a collar — the humblest of microbes, and the closest living relative of every animal that has ever lived. In the choanoflagellate we see the doorstep we all crossed: the lone cell that, prompted by a bacterium, learns to gather into a colony. The threshold between one and many.
